#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing and Exporting Data"
msgstr "Andmete import ja eksport"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:4
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; is able to import and export a wide variety of data files, as well "
"as search various Internet sites for information."
msgstr ""
"&appname; suudab importida ja eksportida väga mitmesuguseid andmefaile, "
"samuti otsida teavet paljudelt internetisaitidelt."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing from the Internet"
msgstr "Import internetist"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:10
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; is able to search various Internet sites using the "
"<interface>Internet Search Dialog</interface>. Entries may be directly "
"imported and added to your current collection. The various providers are "
"configured via the <link linkend=\"data-sources-options\">Data Sources "
"Options</link>."
msgstr ""
"&appname; võib otsida mitmesugustelt internetisaitidelt teavet "
"<interface>internetiotsingu dialoogi</interface> vahendusel. Kirjeid võib "
"otse importida ja lisada oma aktiivsesse kogusse. Eri teabepakkujaid saab "
"seadistada <link linkend=\"data-sources-options\">andmeallikate valikutega</"
"link>."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:14
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Searches may use different criteria: <guilabel>Title</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Person</guilabel>, <guilabel>ISBN</guilabel>, <guilabel>UPC/EAN</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>LCCN</guilabel>, or <guilabel>Keyword</guilabel>. Not "
"all criteria are available for certain data sources. <acronym>ISBN</acronym> "
"and <acronym>LCCN</acronym> values are for books only, while <acronym>UPC</"
"acronym> or <acronym>EAN</acronym> values can apply to any type of item."
msgstr ""
"Otsingutes saab kasutada eri kriteeriume: <guilabel>Pealkiri</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Isik</guilabel>, <guilabel>ISBN</guilabel>, <guilabel>UPC/EAN</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>LCCN</guilabel> või <guilabel>Võtmesõna</guilabel>. "
"Kõigi andmeallikate puhul ei saa kõiki kriteeriume kasutada. <acronym>ISBN</"
"acronym> ja <acronym>LCCN</acronym> väärtused on mõeldud ainult raamatutele, "
"<acronym>UPC</acronym> või <acronym>EAN</acronym> väärtused aga suvalistele "
"esemetele."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:17
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Once a search is initiated, the <guibutton>Search</guibutton> button becomes "
"<guibutton>Stop</guibutton> which will end a search. As results are found, "
"they are added to the list directly under the search box, where selecting an "
"item will show the result without adding it to the collection. Clicking the "
"<guibutton>Add Entry</guibutton> button will add all the selected items to "
"your collection. If the data source has more results than were initially "
"requested, the <guibutton>Get More Results</guibutton> button becomes "
"active. Clicking <guibutton>Clear</guibutton> will remove all the current "
"results and reset the search."
msgstr ""
"Otsingu käivitamisel asendub nupp <guibutton>Otsi</guibutton> nupuga "
"<guibutton>Peata</guibutton>, millele vajutamisel otsing lõpetatakse. "
"Tulemuste leidmisel lisatakse need nimekirja otse otsingukasti all, kus "
"kirje valimisel näeb tulemust, ilma et seda veel lisataks kogusse. Klõps "
"nupule <guibutton>Lisa kirje</guibutton> lisab kõik valitud elemendid "
"kogusse. Kui andmeallikal on rohkem tulemusi, kui esialgu sooviti, muutub "
"aktiivseks nupp <guibutton>Rohkem tulemusi</guibutton>. Nupuga "
"<guibutton>Puhasta</guibutton> saab eemaldada kõik aktiivsed tulemused ja "
"otsingu lähtestada."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: importing-exporting.docbook:21
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<screeninfo>The &appname; <interface>Internet Search Dialog</interface></"
"screeninfo>"
msgstr ""
"<screeninfo>&appname; <interface>internetiotsingu dialoog</interface></"
"screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: importing-exporting.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<phrase>The &appname; <interface>Internet Search Dialog</interface></phrase>"
msgstr ""
"<phrase>&appname; <interface>internetiotsingu dialoog</interface></phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:28
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only entries that match the current collection type will be found. The "
"<guilabel>Description</guilabel> column provides additional information "
"about the entry, in order to differentiate between videos in different "
"formats, or books in different bindings, for example. Once an entry is "
"successfully added to the collection, a checkmark is added to the first "
"column in the list."
msgstr ""
"Ositakse ainult kirjeid, mis sobivad aktiivse kogu tüübiga. Veerg "
"<guilabel>Kirjeldus</guilabel> annab kirje kohta lisateavet, et teha vahet "
"näiteks eri formaadis videodel või eri köites raamatutel. Kui kirje on "
"edukalt kogusse lisatud, lisatakse nimekirja esimesse veergu linnuke."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Multiple entries can be added at once by using the standard &kde; method for "
"multiple selection, which usually involves holding the &Shift; or &Ctrl; key "
"when clicking on an item."
msgstr ""
"Korraga saab lisada ka mitu kirjet, kasutades &kde; tavapärast viisi mitme "
"elemendi valimiseks, milleks tavaliselt on kirjetele klõpsamise ajal klahvi "
"&Shift; või &Ctrl; allhoidmine."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To facilitate the use of barcode scanners, searches can include multiple "
"ISBN/UPC values. Selecting the <guilabel>Multiple ISBN/UPC search</guilabel> "
"check box will disable the search box and enable the <guibutton>Edit ISBN/"
"UPC values...</guibutton> button, which will open a multi-line text entry "
"box. Each ISBN should be entered on a line by itself. After closing the box, "
"each ISBN will be validated for correct formatting. The ISBN validation is "
"able to convert 13-digit EAN values, as well as full <acronym>UPC</acronym> "
"codes, to the proper formatting. The ISBN list may also be read from a text "
"file."
msgstr ""
"Ribakoodilugejate kasutamise lihtsustamiseks võib otsing hõlmata mitut ISBN/"
"UPC väärtust. Ruudukese <guilabel>Mitme ISBN/UPC otsing</guilabel> "
"märkimisel muutub otsisõnakast mitteaktiivseks ning aktiivseks muutub nupp "
"<guibutton>Muuda ISBN/UPC väärtusi</guibutton>, millega saab avada "
"mitmerealist sisestust võimaldava tekstikasti. IGA ISBN peab olema eraldi "
"real. Kasti sulgemise järel kontrollitakse iga ISBN-i vorminduse "
"korrektsust. ISBN-i kontrollimisel saab nii 13-arvulised EAN väärtused kui "
"ka täielikud <acronym>UPC</acronym> koodid teisendada vajalikku vormingusse. "
"ISBN-ide nimekirja võib sisse lugeda ka tekstifailist."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing Data"
msgstr "Andmete import"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:45
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&appname; offers three different actions when importing data. "
#| "<guilabel>Replace current collection</guilabel> will close the current "
#| "collection, and create a new one with the data from the imported file. "
#| "<guilabel>Append to current collection</guilabel> tells &appname; to add "
#| "all the entries in the imported collection to the current one, and to add "
#| "any fields which don't currently exist. The <guilabel>Merge collection</"
#| "guilabel> action is the same as appending, except that each imported "
#| "entry is compared to the current ones, and any identical entries are "
#| "skipped. Future plans include an improved heuristic for identifying "
#| "matching entries, but currently, except for music collections, they must "
#| "be identical for every field. Music collections compare the artist and "
#| "album only, and the tracks are merged for matching entries. The <link "
#| "linkend=\"importing-audio-files\">audio file importer</link> is able to "
#| "correctly build track lists by merging entries."
msgid ""
"&appname; offers three different actions when importing data. "
"<guilabel>Replace current collection</guilabel> will close the current "
"collection, and create a new one with the data from the imported file. "
"<guilabel>Append to current collection</guilabel> tells &appname; to add all "
"the entries in the imported collection to the current one, and to add any "
"fields which don't currently exist. The <guilabel>Merge collection</"
"guilabel> action is the same as appending, except that each imported entry "
"is compared to the current ones, and any identical entries are skipped. "
"&appname; attempts to identify matching entries which are not completely "
"identical by comparing significant fields and will then merge the entries. "
"For example, music collections compare the artist and album, and the tracks "
"would be merged for matching entries. The <link linkend=\"importing-audio-"
"files\">audio file importer</link> is able to correctly build track lists by "
"merging entries."
msgstr ""
"&appname; pakub andmete importimisel kolme toimimisviisi. <guilabel>Aktiivse "
"kogu asendamine</guilabel> sulgeb aktiivse kogu ja loob uue imporditud "
"failist pärit andmetega. <guilabel>Aktiivsele kogule lisamine</guilabel> "
"sunnib &appname; lisama imporditava kogu kõik kirjed aktiivsesse kogusse "
"ning lisama ka kõik väljad, mida seni ei eksisteerinud. <guilabel>Aktiivse "
"koguga liitmine</guilabel> on sarnane lisamisele, ainult et kõiki "
"imporditavaid kirjeid võrreldakse senistega ning kõik identsed kirjed "
"jäetakse vahele. Edaspidi on kavas parandada samaste kirjete tuvastamist, "
"aga praegu peavad need olema identsed kõigi väljade poolest, välja arvatud "
"muusikakogude puhul, mille korral võrreldakse ainult esitajat ja albumit "
"ning kattuvate kirjete puhul palad liidetakse. <link linkend=\"importing-"
"audio-files\">Helifailide importija</link> suudab kirjeid liites luua "
"korrektsed palade nimekirjad."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:50
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Importing from the Internet"
msgid "Importing Data From Other Software"
msgstr "Import internetist"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; can import data directly from a variety of other collection "
"management programs, including <application><ulink url=\"https://gitlab.com/"
"GCstar/GCstar\">GCstar</ulink></application>, <application><ulink url="
"\"https://onmyshelf.app\">OnMyShelf</ulink></application>, "
"<application><ulink url=\"https://www.datacrow.net/\">Data Crow</ulink></"
"application>, <application><ulink url=\"https://github.com/mvz/alexandria-"
"book-collection-manager\">Alexandria</ulink></application>, "
"<application><ulink url=\"https://www.delicious-monster.com\">Delicious "
"Library</ulink></application>, <application><ulink url=\"https://www."
"collectorz.com\">Collectorz</ulink></application>, <application><ulink url="
"\"http://www.antp.be/software/moviecatalog/\">Ant Movie Catalog</ulink></"
"application>, <application><ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Referencer\">Referencer</ulink></application>, and <application><ulink url="
"\"https://launchpad.net/griffith\">Griffith</ulink></application>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:66
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Importing GCstar Data"
msgid "Importing Other Data Formats"
msgstr "GCstari andmete import"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; can import data from a variety of other file formats, including "
"<acronym>CSV</acronym>, bibtex, audio discs and files, <acronym>MODS</"
"acronym>, &PDF;, and <acronym>RIS</acronym>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing &appname; Data"
msgstr "&appname; andmete import"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:72
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Other &appname; data files may be imported. Replacing the current "
#| "collection by importing a &appname; file is the same thing as just "
#| "opening the file itself. The value of importing &appname; data is "
#| "primarily for appending or merging two collections together."
msgid ""
"Other &appname; data files may be imported directly. Replacing the current "
"collection by importing a &appname; file is the same thing as just opening "
"the file itself. The value of importing &appname; data is primarily for "
"appending or merging two collections together."
msgstr ""
"Importida saab ka teisi &appname; andmefaile. Aktiivse kogu asendamine "
"&appname; faili importides on samaväärne faili avamisega. &appname; andmete "
"importimine on eelkõige mõttekas andmete lisamiseks või kahe kogu "
"ühendamiseks."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing CSV Data"
msgstr "CSV-andmete import"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:80
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Comma-separated values (<acronym>CSV</acronym>) are a common way of "
"importing and exporting tabular data. Each field value is separated by a "
"comma, with one entry per line. The field titles may be included in the "
"first line. The CSV importer is not limited to using a comma as the "
"separator. Any character or string may be used."
msgstr ""
"Komadega eraldatud väärtuste (<acronym>CSV</acronym>) kasutamine on levinud "
"viis tabelisse korraldatud andmete importimiseks ja eksportimiseks. Iga "
"välja väärtus on eraldatud komaga, üks kirje rea kohta. Väljade nimed võivad "
"olla esimesel real. CSV importija ei ole aga piiratud komaga: eraldajaks "
"võib kasutada mis tahes tähte või stringi."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: importing-exporting.docbook:85
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The CSV Import Dialog</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>CSV importimise dialoog</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: importing-exporting.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The CSV Import Dialog</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>CSV importimise dialoog</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:92
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First, select the type of collection that you are importing. If you are "
"appending or merging to your open collection, the type is limited to your "
"current collection type. If the first line of the CSV file contains the "
"field titles, click the check box and the importer will automatically "
"compare the titles against the fields in the current collection. If a field "
"title matches, the header for that column changes to show that the column "
"has been assigned to that field. If the file uses a delimiter other than a "
"comma, be sure to change that option accordingly."
msgstr ""
"Kõigepealt vali imporditava kogu tüüp. Kui tegemist on aktiivsele kogule "
"lisamise või sellega liitmisega, siis on tüübiks juba ette valitud aktiivse "
"kogu tüüp. Kui CSV-faili esimene rida sisaldab väljade pealkirju, märgista "
"vastav ruuduke ning importija võrdleb automaatselt pealkirju aktiivse kogu "
"väljadega. Kui välja pealkiri kattub, muutub selle veeru päis näitamaks, et "
"veerg on omistatud sellele väljale. Kui fail kasutab mõnda muud eraldajat "
"kui koma, märgi kindlasti ka vastav valik."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:96
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In order for &appname; to properly import the file, it must know which field "
"corresponds to each column. <emphasis>If the column only has a number in the "
"header, the data in that column will not be imported.</emphasis> You should "
"assign fields to each column by selecting a column, either by clicking in it "
"or changing the column number itself, then selecting the field to assign "
"from the drop down box and clicking the <guibutton>Assign Field</guibutton> "
"button. If you need to add a new field to the collection, the last item in "
"the drop down box opens the <link linkend=\"fields-dialog"
"\"><interface>Collection Fields Dialog</interface></link>."
msgstr ""
"Et &appname; saaks faili korrektselt importida, peab ta teadma, milline väli "
"vastab millisele veerule. <emphasis>Kui veeru päises on ainult number, selle "
"veeru andmeid ei impordita.</emphasis> Sa peaksid omistama väljad igale "
"veerule, valides veeru kas sellele klõpsates või muutes veeru numbrit ennast "
"ning siis valides omistatava välja rippmenüüst ja klõpsates nupule "
"<guibutton>Omista väli</guibutton>. Kui on vaja lisada kogusse uus väli, "
"avab rippmenüü viimane käsk <link linkend=\"fields-dialog\"><interface>kogu "
"väljade dialoogi</interface></link>."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:100
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Only the first five lines of the imported CSV file are shown in the "
#| "dialog."
msgid ""
"For compactness, only the first five lines of the imported CSV file are "
"shown in the dialog. However, all the lines in the file will be imported."
msgstr "Dialoogis näidatakse ainult imporditava CSV-faili esimest viit rida."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing Audio &CD; Data"
msgstr "Heli-&CD; andmete import"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:109
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&appname; is able to use the <ulink url=\"http://freedb.org\">freedb.org</"
#| "ulink> service to lookup information about a &CD;, including the track "
#| "list. Depending on your distribution, settings for access to the service "
#| "may be set in the &kde; &systemsettings;. The &CD; artist, title, genre, "
#| "year, and track listing are all added."
msgid ""
"&appname; is able to use the <ulink url=\"http://gnudb.org\">freedb.org</"
"ulink> service to lookup information about a &CD;, including the track list. "
"Depending on your distribution, settings for access to the service may be "
"set in the &kde; &systemsettings;. The &CD; artist, title, genre, year, and "
"track listing are all added."
msgstr ""
"&appname; võib kasutada <ulink url=\"http://freedb.org\">freedb.org-i</"
"ulink> teenust teabe hankimiseks &CD; kohta, kaasa arvatud selle radade "
"nimekiri. Sõltuvalt distributsioonist võib olla vajalik määrata teenuse "
"kasutamise seadistusi &kde; Süsteemi seadistustes. Lisatakse nii &CD; "
"esitaja, pealkiri, žanr, aasta kui ka radade nimekiri."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In addition, if the disc contains &CD;-Text, that information is read and "
"added to the imported entry."
msgstr ""
"Kui plaat peaks sisaldama &CD;-teksti, loetakse sisse ka see teave ning "
"lisatakse imporditavale kirjele."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing Audio File Metadata"
msgstr "Helifaili metaandmete import"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; is able to scan a folder and read the tags for common audio file "
"formats, such as <literal role=\"extension\">mp3</literal> and <literal role="
"\"extension\">ogg</literal>. The songs are entered in a music collection, "
"where each entry is an album. If the song files contain the track number, "
"the song name is inserted in the correct spot in the track list. The artist "
"and genre information is also added to the entry. If the song tags contain "
"comments, they are appended to the comments field in the entry, preceded by "
"the file name."
msgstr ""
"&appname; võib läbi uurida kataloogi ning lugeda sealt välja levinumate "
"helifailivormingute, näiteks <literal role=\"extension\">mp3</literal>- ja "
"<literal role=\"extension\">ogg</literal>-failide sildid. Laulud "
"sisestatakse muusikalogusse, kus iga kirje on album. Kui laulufailid "
"sisaldavad raja numbrit, lisatakse laulu nimi radade nimekirjas õigesse "
"kohta. Kirjele lisatakse ka teave esitaja ja žanri kohta. Kui laulu sildid "
"sisaldavad kommentaare, lisatakse need kirje kommentaariväljale, mille ees "
"seisab failinimi."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:128
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In addition, if a folder contains a <filename>.directory</filename> file and "
"the folder name matches an album title, the <literal>Icon</literal> entry in "
"the desktop file is used as the cover image for the album."
msgstr ""
"Kui kataloog peaks sisaldama faili <filename>.directory</filename> ja "
"kataloogi nimi kattub albumi pealkirjaga, kasutatakse desktop-faili kirjet "
"<literal>Icon</literal> albumi kaanepildina."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:132
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The audio file metadata importer can recursively scan a folder to find "
#| "all audio files in any subfolder, though symbolic links are not followed. "
#| "&appname; uses the <ulink url=\"http://developer.kde.org/~wheeler/taglib."
#| "html\">TagLib library</ulink> for reading the audio file metadata, and so "
#| "can import data from any file type that TagLib understands."
msgid ""
"The audio file metadata importer can recursively scan a folder to find all "
"audio files in any subfolder, though symbolic links are not followed. "
"&appname; uses the <ulink url=\"https://taglib.org\">TagLib library</ulink> "
"for reading the audio file metadata, and so can import data from any file "
"type that TagLib understands."
msgstr ""
"Helifaili metaandmete importija võib rekursiivselt läbi uurida kataloogi, et "
"leida kõik helifailid kõigis alamkataloogides, ehkki nimeviitasid sel puhul "
"ei järgita. &appname; kasutab helifaili metaandmete lugemiseks <ulink url="
"\"http://developer.kde.org/~wheeler/taglib.html\">TagLibi teeki</ulink>, "
"mistõttu ta võib importida kõigi failitüüpide andmeid, mida TagLib vähegi "
"tunnustab."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing Bibtex Data"
msgstr "Bibtexi andmete import"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:141
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bibtex\">Bibtex</ulink> is a "
#| "bibliography format used with the LaTeX document preparation system. "
#| "Various type of bibliographic references may be included in the file. "
#| "&appname; imports bibtex files as a Bibliographic collection."
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bibtex\">Bibtex</ulink> is a "
"bibliography format used with the LaTeX document preparation system. Various "
"type of bibliographic references may be included in the file. &appname; "
"imports bibtex files as a <link linkend=\"bibliography\">Bibliographic "
"collection</link>."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bibtex\">Bibtex</ulink> on "
"bibliograafiavorming, mida kasutab LaTeXi dokumentide ettevalmistamise "
"süsteem. Failis võivad sisalduda eri tüüpi bibliograafilised viited. "
"&appname; impordib bibtex-failid bibliograafiakoguna."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the bibtex importer encounters fields in the file which are not in the "
"default bibliography collection, they are added as <link linkend=\"line"
"\">Simple Text</link> fields, with two exceptions. If the field value "
"contains more than 100 characters, it becomes a <link linkend=\"para"
"\">Paragraph</link> field. If the field value appears to contain a &URL; or "
"a file reference, then a <link linkend=\"url\">&URL;</link> field is "
"created. &appname; uses an internal copy of the <ulink url=\"http://www.gerg."
"ca/software/btOOL/\">btparse library</ulink> for parsing the bibtex files."
msgstr ""
"Kui bibtexi importija kohtab failis välju, mida ei leidu vaikimisi "
"bibliograafiakogus, lisatakse need väljatüübina <link linkend=\"line"
"\">Tavaline tekst</link>, välja arvatud kaks erandit. Kui välja väärtus "
"sisaldab üle 100 märgi, lisatakse see väljatüübina <link linkend=\"para"
"\">Lõik</link>. Kui välja väärtus paistab sisaldavat &URL;-i või "
"failiviidet, lisatakse see väljatüübina <link linkend=\"url\">&URL;</link>. "
"&appname; kasutab bibtex-failide parsimiseks sisemist <ulink url=\"http://"
"www.gerg.ca/software/btOOL/\">btparse teegi</ulink> koopiat."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"http://bibtexml.sf.net\">Bibtexml</ulink> is an &XML; "
"representation of bibtex data, and the data from the imported bibtexml file "
"is treated in the same way as bibtex data would be."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://bibtexml.sf.net\">Bibtexml</ulink> on bibtex-andmed "
"&XML;-i kujul ning bibtexml-failist imporditavaid andmeid koheldakse "
"samamoodi nagu bibtex-andmeid."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing MODS Data"
msgstr "MODS-i andmete import"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:157
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<acronym><ulink url=\"http://www.loc.gov/standards/mods/\">MODS</ulink></"
