#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:214
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing File Listings"
msgstr "Failinimekirjade import"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:216
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The best way to create a <link linkend=\"file-catalog\">File Catalog</"
#| "link> is to import the contents of a folder. The folder may be searched "
#| "recursively, to add all files found within. This importer is most useful "
#| "for backup listings and media cataloging, such as &CD; or <acronym>DVD</"
#| "acronym> listings. In addition, image previews of the file contents may "
#| "be generated, although it can take some time to read a large number of "
#| "files. The file previews are same as those shown in the &kde; file "
#| "manager."
msgid ""
"&tellico; can scan folders to import file information, primarily to create a "
"<link linkend=\"file-catalog\">File Catalog</link> collection. The folder "
"may be searched recursively, to add all files found within. This importer is "
"most useful for backup listings and media cataloging, such as &CD; or "
"<acronym>DVD</acronym> listings. In addition, image previews of the file "
"contents may be generated. The file previews are same as those shown in the "
"&kde; file manager."
msgstr ""
"Parim viis <link linkend=\"file-catalog\">failikataloogi</link> loomiseks on "
"kataloogi sisu importimine. Kataloogi võib rekursiivselt läbi uurida, et "
"lisatakse kõik selles leitavad failid. See importija on eelkõige kasulik "
"tagavarakoopiate ning andmekandjate, näiteks &CD;-de või <acronym>DVD</"
"acronym>-de sisu kataloogimiseks. Lisaks võib genereerida failisisu "
"eelvaatlused, kuigi suurema hulga failide korral võtab nende lugemine "
"omajagu aega. Failide eelvaatlused on samasugused nagu &kde; failihalduris."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Folders with ebook files and video files may also be imported as book and "
"video collections. File metadata can be read, and for video files, any "
"existing <literal role=\"extension\">nfo</literal> files are used to "
"complete the video entry information."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:227
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing &XML; Data via XSLT"
msgstr "&XML;-andmete import XSLT vahendusel"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Any &XML; file may be imported into &appname; provided an &XSL; stylesheet "
"is available to convert the file to &appname; format. &appname; "
"automatically loads the stylesheet and performs the &xslt; processing needed "
"to load the file."
msgstr ""
"Mis tahes &XML;-faili saab importida &appname;sse, kui &XSL;-laaditabel on "
"vähegi suuteline teisendama faili &appname; vormingusse. &appname; laadib "
"laaditabeli automaatselt ning sooritab faili laadimiseks vajaliku &xslt; "
"töötluse."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "Drag and Drop"
msgstr "Lohistamine"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:239
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Dragging data files to the main &appname; window and dropping them will "
#| "import the files, just as if the <link linkend=\"importing\">import "
#| "command</link> was made from the menus. Drag and drop works for the "
#| "following file formats: Tellico, Bibtex, RIS, and PDF. Importing multiple "
#| "files at once is also supported."
msgid ""
"Dragging data files to the main &appname; window and dropping them will "
"import the files, just as if the <link linkend=\"importing\">import command</"
"link> was made from the menus. Drag and drop works for the following file "
"formats: Tellico, Bibtex, RIS, &PDF;, and EPub. Importing multiple files at "
"once is also supported."
msgstr ""
"Andmefailide lohistamisega &appname; peaaknasse saab neid samamoodi "
"importida nagu menüü <link linkend=\"importing\">importimiskäskudega</link>. "
"Lohistamine toimib järgmiste failivormingute puhul: Tellico, Bibtex, RIS ja "
"PDF. Toetatud on ka mitme faili importimine korraga."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:241
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "So, for example, if you want to catalog several <link linkend=\"importing-"
#| "pdf\">PDF files</link>, select them in the file manager and drag them to "
#| "the &appname; window. &appname; will import as much metadata from the "
#| "files as it can, and then fetch additional information from various "
#| "configured Internet sources."
msgid ""
"So, for example, if you want to catalog several <link linkend=\"importing-pdf"
"\">&PDF; files</link>, select them in the file manager and drag them to the "
"&appname; window. &appname; will import as much metadata from the files as "
"it can, and then fetch additional information from various configured "
"Internet sources."
msgstr ""
"Kui näiteks soovid kataloogida mitu <link linkend=\"importing-pdf\">PDF-"
"faili</link>, vali need failihalduris ja lohista &appname; aknasse. "
"&appname; impordib failidest nii palju metaandmeid kui võimalik ning hangib "
"seejärel lisateavet erinevatest seadistatud internetiallikatest."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting Data"
msgstr "Andmete eksport"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:248
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When exporting the data in the collection, the entry values may be exported "
"as entered, or with the <link linkend=\"field-formatting\">automatic "
"formatting</link> provided by &appname;. Additionally, the export may be "
"limited to the currently selected entries of the collection as well, where "
"the <link linkend=\"status-bar\">statusbar</link> shows the number of "
"selected entries."
msgstr ""
"Kogu andmete eksportimisel võidakse kirjete väärtused eksportida sellisena, "
"nagu need on sisestatud, või kasutades &appname; pakutavat <link linkend="
"\"field-formatting\">automaatset vormindamist</link>. Lisaks võib eksporti "
"piirata ka kogus parajasti valitud kirjetega, mille puhul valitud kirjete "
"arvu võib näha <link linkend=\"status-bar\">olekuribal</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Exported text files, such as Bibtex or CSV, may use the Unicode (UTF-8) "
"character encoding, or the current locale of the operating system."
msgstr ""
"Tekstifailide, näiteks Bibtex- või CSV-failide eksportimisel võib kasutada "
"nii Unicode'i (UTF-8) kodeeringut kui ka operatsioonisüsteemi aktiivset "
"lokaati."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: importing-exporting.docbook:257
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>General Export Options</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Üldised eksportimisvalikud</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: importing-exporting.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>General Export Options</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Üldised eksportimisvalikud</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:265
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting &XML;"
msgstr "Eksport &XML;-ina"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:267
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The file format for &appname; data is a zipped &XML; file. Exporting to "
"&XML; merely creates the &XML; file without zipping it. Images may be "
"included in the &XML; file as base64-encoded data in an image element, but "
"doing so can create very large text files."
msgstr ""
"&appname; andmete failivorming on zip-pakendusega on &XML;-fail. Eksport "
"&XML;-ina tähendab lihtsalt &XML;-faili loomist ilma seda zip-pakendamata. "
"Pildid saab &XML;-faili kaasata base64 kodeeringus andmetena elemendis "
"image, kuid sel moel tekivad väga suured tekstifailid."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:273
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting Zip"
msgstr "Eksport Zipina"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:275
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The standard file format for &appname; is a zipped file, contained the "
#| "&XML; collection file, and optionally, all the images referenced in the "
#| "collection. If the images are being stored in the application folder "
#| "instead, exporting to a Zip file will create a self-contained data file, "
#| "which includes all the images in the collection."
msgid ""
"The standard file format for &appname; is a zipped file, containing the "
"&XML; collection file, and optionally, all the images referenced in the "
"collection. If the images are being stored in the application folder "
"instead, exporting to a Zip file will create a self-contained data file, "
"which includes all the images in the collection."
msgstr ""
"&appname; standardne failivorming on zip-pakendusega fail, mis sisaldab "
"&XML;-kogufaili ja lisavõimalusega kõiki pilte, millele kogus viidatakse. "
"Kui pildid on salvestatud rakenduse kataloogi, luuakse eksportimisel Zipina "
"autonoomne andmefail, mis sisaldab kõiki kogus leiduvaid pilte."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting &HTML;"
msgstr "Eksport &HTML;-ina"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:283
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &HTML; export uses the <filename>tellico2html.xsl</filename> stylesheet. "
"Images are exported to a folder with the same name as the exported &HTML; "
"file with <emphasis><filename>_files</filename></emphasis> appended."
msgstr ""
"Eksportimisel &HTML;-ina kasutatakse laaditabelit <filename>tellico2html."
"xsl</filename>. Pildid eksporditakse kataloogi sama nimega nagu eksporditav "
"&HTML;-fail, lisades <emphasis><filename>_files</filename></emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:287
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default format is similar to the printed output, and allows various "
"options for modifying the &HTML;. Field headers may be printed at the top of "
"each column, but unfortunately, &kde; does not yet allow the table headers "
"to be repeated on each page. The entries may be grouped as in the "
"<interface>Group View</interface>, as well."
msgstr ""
"Vaikevorming on sarnane trükkimisväljundile ning võimaldab mitmesuguseid "
"&HTML;-i modifitseerivaid valikuid. Väljade päiseid saab lasta näidata iga "
"veeru kohal, kuid paraku ei võimalda &kde; veel korrata tabeli päiseid igal "
"leheküljel. Kirjeid saab rühmitada samamoodi nagu <interface>rühmavaates</"
"interface>."

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:291
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Additionally, individual files may be created for each entry in the "
"collection, with links created in the top-level &HTML; file. The entry files "
"will be created in the same folder as the images. The entry &HTML; files "
"will use the current stylesheet template, as shown in the <interface>Entry "
"View</interface>."
msgstr ""
"Lisaks võib igale kogu kirjele luua eraldi faili, mille lingid sisalduvad "
"tipptaseme &HTML;-failis. Kirjefailid luuakse piltidega samasse kataloogi. "
"Kirjete &HTML;-failid kasutavad aktiivset laaditabeli malli, nagu seda näeb "
"<interface>kirjevaates</interface>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: importing-exporting.docbook:296
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>&HTML; Export Options</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>&HTML;-ina eksportimise valikud</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: importing-exporting.docbook:299
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&HTML; Export Options</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&HTML;-ina eksportimise valikud</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting CSV"
msgstr "Eksport CSV-na"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:307
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Comma-separated values (CSV) are a common way of importing and exporting "
"tabular data. Each field value is separated by a comma, with one entry per "
"line. The field titles may be included as headers in the first line. Any "
"character or string other than a comma may also be used to delimit the "
"fields."
msgstr ""
"Komadega eraldatud väärtused (CSV) on tavapärane tabelisse korraldatud "
"andmete importimis- ja eksportimisviis. Kõigi väljade väärtused on eraldatud "
"komaga, igal real on üks kirje. Väljade pealkirjad võivad olla esitatud "
"päistena esimesel real. Väljade eraldamiseks võib kasutada ka mis tahes muid "
"märke või stringe peale komade."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: importing-exporting.docbook:312
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>CSV Export Options</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>CSV-na eksportimise valikud</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: importing-exporting.docbook:315
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>CSV Export Options</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>CSV-na eksportimise valikud</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:321
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting Alexandria"
msgstr "Eksport Alexandriana"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:323
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<application><ulink url=\"http://alexandria.rubyforge.net\">Alexandria</"
#| "ulink></application> is a book collection manager for the <ulink url="
#| "\"http://www.gnome.org\">GNOME</ulink> desktop environment. &appname; is "
#| "able to export a limited subset of book collection fields to the default "
#| "Alexandria data location."
msgid ""
"<application><ulink url=\"https://github.com/mvz/alexandria-book-collection-"
"manager\">Alexandria</ulink></application> is a book collection manager for "
"the <ulink url=\"http://www.gnome.org\">GNOME</ulink> desktop environment. "
"&appname; is able to export a limited subset of book collection fields to "
"the default Alexandria data location."
msgstr ""
"<application><ulink url=\"http://alexandria.rubyforge.net\">Alexandria</"
"ulink></application> on raamatute kogude haldur <ulink url=\"http://www."
"gnome.org\">GNOME</ulink> töökeskkonnas. &appname; on suuteline eksportima "
"piiratud hulgal raamatute kogu välju Alexandria vaikimisi andmete asukohta."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:330
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting ONIX"
msgstr "Eksport ONIX-ina"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"http://www.editeur.org/onix.html\">ONIX</ulink> is an &XML; "
"format for representing and communicating book industry product information, "
"primarily for book vendors. &appname; can export book collections using a "
"small subset of ONIX."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://www.editeur.org/onix.html\">ONIX</ulink> on &XML;-"
"vorming raamatutööstuse tooteteabe väljendamiseks ja vahetamiseks, mis on "
"peamiselt välja töötatud raamatukaupmeeste huvides. &appname; võib "
"eksportida raamatute kogusid, kasutades vähesel hulgal ONIX-i võimalusi."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting Bibtex"
msgstr "Eksport Bibtexina"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:341
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When exporting to <ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bibtex\">Bibtex</"
"ulink>, the field values may be escaped with braces or quotation marks. If "
"any string macros are used in the collection, they may optionally be "
"exported as macros or expanded. For &URL; fields, &appname; may enclose the "
"field values with the <literal>\\url{...}</literal> tag. Finally, entries "
"with no citation key may be skipped rather than have &appname; auto-generate "
"the key."
msgstr ""
"Eksportimisel <ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bibtex\">Bibtexina</"
"ulink> võib väljade väärtusi varjestada sulgude või jutumärkidega. Kui kogus "
"on kasutatud stringimakrosid, võib neid eksportida nii makrodena kui ka "
"laiendatult. &URL;-väljade korral võib &appname; sulustada väljade väärtused "
"sildiga <literal>\\url{...}</literal>. Kirjed, millel puudub viitevõti, võib "
"lasta vahele jätta, kuid võib lasta ka &appname;l neile automaatselt võtme "
"genereerida."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: importing-exporting.docbook:348
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Bibtex Export Options</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Bibtexina eksportimise valikud</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: importing-exporting.docbook:351
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Bibtex Export Options</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Bibtexina eksportimise valikud</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:357
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting GCstar"
msgstr "GCstari eksport"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:359
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<application><ulink url=\"http://www.gcstar.org\">GCstar</ulink></"
"application> is another movie collection manager. &appname; is able to "
"export most collection types to a GCstar data file."
msgstr ""
"<application><ulink url=\"http://www.gcstar.org\">GCstar</ulink></"
"application> on veel üks filmikogude haldur. &appname; suudab eksportida "
"piiratud hulgal videokogu välju GCstari andmefaili."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:366
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exporting &XML; via &xslt;"
msgstr "Eksport &XML;-ina &xslt; vahendusel"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:368
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Finally, &appname; is able to process its internal &XML; representation of "
"the collection data through an external &XSL; stylesheet before exporting. "
"This type of export may be useful for generating text reports or other file "
"types."
msgstr ""
"Lõpuks võib &appname; töödelda oma kogu andmete sisemist esitust &XML;ina "
"välise &XSL;-laaditabeli abil, enne kui see eksportida. Seda laadi "
"eksportimine võib olla kasulik tekstiaruannete või muud tüüpi failide "
"genereerimiseks."

#. Tag: title
#: importing-exporting.docbook:376
#, no-c-format
msgid "Working With Citations"
msgstr "Viidete kasutamine"

#. Tag: para
#: importing-exporting.docbook:377
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When working with a <link linkend=\"bibliography\">bibliography</link>, "
"citations for the currently selected entries may be generated and used in "
"various other applications. A citation in bibtex format can be copied to the "
"clipboard, and then pasted in a latex file. Bibtex citations can also be "
"pushed to an external application such as <application>LyX</application> or "
"<application>Kile</application> using the so-called <emphasis><link linkend="
"\"hidden-bibtex-options\">lyxpipe</link></emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"bibliography\">Bibliograafia</link> puhul võib genereerida "
"parajasti valitud kirjete viited ning neid kasutada mitmes muus rakenduses. "
"Bibtexi vormingus viite võib kopeerida lõikepuhvrisse ja asetada sealt "
"LaTeXi faili. Bibtexi viiteid võib läkitada ka sellistesse välistesse "
"rakendustesse, nagu <application>LyX</application> või <application>Kile</"
"application>, kasutades selleks niinimetatud <emphasis><link linkend="
"\"hidden-bibtex-options\">lyxpipe'i</link></emphasis>."

